reporter: libreport-2.9.1 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/bin/gnome-font-viewer --gapplication-service crash_function: gtk_header_bar_pack executable: /usr/bin/gnome-font-viewer journald_cursor: s=a63dfcab0f484b6ab1b8ef47c7694bd2;i=7f4b;b=2168ab84b6e5430e9b29bae59352ced7;m=e181620a;t=54fb4f7c41370;x=ee3ee8b08252935d kernel: 4.11.0-2.fc26.x86_64 package: gnome-font-viewer-3.24.0-1.fc26 reason: gnome-font-viewer killed by signal 11 rootdir: / runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000

Reported upstream: https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=782738
We also identified the commit which most likely causes the crash.

Proposed as a Blocker for 26-final by Fedora user eischmann using the blocker tracking app because:
I'm proposing this as a release blocker for Final because GNOME Font Viewer is a pre-installed application and opening a font file to view and install is a fundamental feature of it.
